title: Rock Insider | By Don Thrasher
text:
​It’s been a productive 2015 for Dayton-based indie rockers, Good Luck Year, which dropped its second release of the year in September. The new EP, “Tinder for the Fire,” is the follow-up to the band’s self-titled EP from January.
The group, which played its first show in July 2014, features Matt Shetler (vocals, guitar), Justin Smith (guitar), Tesia Mallory (vocals, keyboards), Josh Guild (keyboards), Jason Thompson (bass) and Cole Howell (drums). Shetler, Mallory and Howell recently discussed the evolution of Good Luck Year.
Continue reading on MyDaytonDailyNews.com. »
